ddition to slaughtering others as he did me, his total health was on a slow incline. Finally, after about 4 deaths, I invis'd myself, walked into the arena, and found him sitting on the floor at 30% health. I manuevered behind him, BS'd him, and finished him off before he realized what happened. And the entire zone cheered, and it was I who had truly won.<br>
<br>
Lesson learned - Death is a good thing when nothing is lost, but tactical advantage is gained.<br>
<br>
After the crowd settled and had started leaving, most of those that remained continued to fight in the truest of cowardly fashions. And I have yet to allow a coward to survive. I spotted a young druid of many years younger than I run into the Arena, nuke someone, and then flee before giving his victim a chance to fight back. So, keeping him in sight, I invis'd myself and stepped onto his normal traveling path. He stepped in, cast his spell, got backstabbed, got pierced, and ran. Seeing his lack of strategical skills, I stepped to the side of the entrance and awaited his next arrival. Just a few seconds later, he stepped into the arena, cast, Got backstabbed again from the same unknown assailant, got pierced multiple times AGAIN, and again, ran like the coward he was. So, what did I do? I stepped to the OTHER side of the entrance and awaited his arrival which would be his death. Thinking he was as sly as I, he stepped to the other side of the arena, began casting, got backstabbed for the 3rd time, got pierced again, and didn't survive to run. One coward dead, one victory to those with honor. (rogue with honor? yes. It's the one thing that separates a rogue from a thief)<br>
<br>
And those are my victories in the Arena. both fights which I remember with pride.<br>
<br>
Maldicion Del'Borracho<br>
51 Rake<br>
Mithaniel Marr <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujoonlingshadowstryker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JoonLingShadowStryker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/01 10:58:54 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/joonlingshadowstryker/Joonstamp.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: FFA in the Arena</span><hr size=1> Very nice but I have one question: why didn't you hide/sneak after the first death? <p><big>
