I'll try very hard to not insult your intelligence, but I will most certainly fail miserably.<br>
<br>
First of all, just because I didn't say that I did, that doesn't mean that I didn't. I just found no point in stating what should be the stupidly obvious. Of course EVERY Rogue is going to Sneak/Hide. It's the most useful tool we have in our vast collection. That being said, let's explain the basics of Sneak/Hide and targetting.<br>
<br>
I checked and unless my source was incorrect, Necro's do not get See Invis, so we can rule that out.<br>
So, let's explain in detail how each of my encounters with the necro went after my first death.<br>
<br>
1) Sneak/Hide<br>
2) Drag corpse out of arena and loot it<br>
3) Sneak/Hide<br>
4) Go back into arena, find Necro<br>
5) Manuever behind unsuspecting Necro<br>
6) Backstab and commence attacking<br>
...Guess Who's name is on Necro's targetting now?<br>
...If Necro had another on targetting already, solution is simple. hit &quot;Esc&quot; to clear targetting and wait for the next pierce to land so my name is on targetting.<br>
7) Necro casts his Darkness spell<br>
...For those of you who may not have noticed (Joonling perhaps), a Rogue's piercing does virtually NOTHING to interrupt casting. Especially when the caster has a channeling skill of 200.<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Darkness spell lands.<br>
9) Necro finishes me off with more DoT's and his pet.<br>
10) LOADING...PLEASE WAIT<br>
11) See step 1<br>
<br>
I hope this clarifies up the situation and answers your question, Joonling. Again, I hope that I haven't insulted YOUR intelligence any more than you've insulted MINE.<br>
